  "text": "since the Hermite functions are (to within the factor of i) their own transform. This implies that the wave is not a single latitudinal wavenumber as in [CITATION_1] , but is rather a wave packet. Furthermore, it is not a spectrum which has a tall, narrow peak about some particular wavenumber m = m 0, as is required to rigorously justify the wave-tracing arguments of Yarnagata (1976) , but is rather a disturbance with a broad latitudinal Fourier spectrum.",
